  "texts": [
    "Some large-scale generative language models go through a fine-tuning step where human raters provide specific feedback used to train them to follow instructions and align with ethical principles and product design goals [42].",
    "These include Sparrow [43], Anthropic's assistant [44], and Instruct-GPT [45], the latter of which was the basis for the GPT-3.5 system which we used in this paper.",
    "Fine-tuning can be accomplished through a variety of techniques, the most prominent being Reinforcement Learning from Human Feedback (RLHF).",
    "It involves human raters selecting which of several possible model responses they prefer.",
    "The raters are not asked the subjective question of which response they themselves prefer, but rather are given a specific checklist of product design goals to apply in making their judgments."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
